cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about machine comprehension and its application to sequence-to-sequence tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel architecture for improving the performance of baseline models, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The experiments involve neural machine translation, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also achieves state-of-the-art results on the Gigaword dataset, indicating it could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
